'''Emissary of the Void''' is a six-part serialized [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] novella written by [[Greg Keyes]]. It is considered the tenth installment of the [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''New Jedi Order'' series]]. The first three parts of the story were printed in ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' magazine [[Star Wars Gamer 8|8]]-[[Star Wars Gamer 10|10]] until the end of the title's run and the final three parts were later published in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine [[Star Wars Insider 62|62]]-[[Star Wars Insider 64|64]]. The first three parts of the story were made freely available online at [[StarWars.com]], prior to the printing of the final three chapters in ''Insider''. All six chapters were later reprinted on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] for members only.<ref name="TERC" /> To this date, ''Emissary of the Void'' is the only ''New Jedi Order'' tale not to be collected in print, in its entirety, or released as an eBook.

==Plot summary==
It is a dark time for the [[New Republic]] as well as the entire galaxy. The [[Yuuzhan Vong War]] continues to rage — now in its second year. In the wake of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War|Yuuzhan Vong Invasion]], which began at Vector Prime and has now spread across the entire Outer Rim; whole systems have been destroyed and trillions of lives lost. No species is spared in the wake of this brutal wave of death and destruction.

The Jedi Order remains the last glimmer of hope for the imperiled galaxy; even though their Jedi abilities are confounded by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]], who cannot be sensed through the [[The Force|Force]]. Fortunately, the Jedi quickly learn that these extra-galactic invaders are susceptible to some Force-based attacks, which has allowed them to slow the relentless advance of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]].

[[Tsavong Lah]], the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Warmaster]]<nowiki/>, has countered the Jedi threat by proclaiming that he will halt his invasion of the galaxy if all Jedi are captured. This proclamation has resulted in Jedi being hunted down across the galaxy — either to be killed or captured by the Yuuzhan Vong, the desperate citizens of the galaxy, or the paramilitary group known as the '[[Peace Brigade]]'.

With the assistance of the [[Peace Brigade]], the Yuuzhan Vong have now overrun Yavin 4 and the [[Jedi Praxeum]] located there; resulting in many Jedi killed or captured and only a handful escaping the massacre. Young [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]] and [[Tahiri Veila|Tahiri]] manage to escape from their captors — but not unscathed. Anakin is gravely wounded and Tahiri has been "[[Shaping protocol|shaped]]" by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] prior to their escape.

In the aftermath of the Jedi Praxeum's destruction, the remaining Jedi continue to be hunted — by friend and foe alike — and have once again gone into hiding. The [[Yuuzhan Vong]] onslaught now seems unstoppable and without the Jedi to defend it, the future of the [[New Republic]] and the galaxy, itself, is bleak.

Set during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], the story revolves around the adventures of rescue pilot [[Uldir Lochett]] and hunted [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Klin-Fa Gi]].

==Continuity==
Emissary Of The Void begins after ''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory I: Conquest]]'' with the first four parts taking place before ''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth|Edge Of Victory II: Rebirth]]''. The final two parts of ''Emissary of the Void'' weave their way throughout the events of ''Rebirth''.

For the later online reprints, "The War on Wayland" incorrectly had "The" dropped from the title, becoming "War on Wayland".

